The paper discusses the design of tools and data pipelines for explainable B2B machine learning systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on the organizational context and secondary audiences suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) perspective. The use of custom ML-based chatbots for recruitment implies a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the mention of chatbots suggests a potential application in natural language processing (cs.CL).
